      "requirement": "A client can search for a suitable project category.",
      "evidence_quote": "If it is a client, they first search for a suitable project category."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "An BPO organization can accept or decline a request from a client.",
      "evidence_quote": "Then, the BPO organization can either accept or decline the request. If it is declined, it ends there."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "A client can decide to proceed with an accepted project or reject it.",
      "evidence_quote": "If the BPO accepts, the client then decides whether to proceed or reject it. If the client rejects it, it ends."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "The project status is updated after acceptance by both parties.",
      "evidence_quote": "After that, the project status is updated."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "A client can track the progress of a project.",
      "evidence_quote": "The client may choose to track the progress, while the BPO organization can update the progress."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "An BPO organization can update the progress of a project.",
      "evidence_quote": "The client may choose to track the progress, while the BPO organization can update the progress."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "A final project is uploaded once work is completed.",
      "evidence_quote": "Once the work is completed, the final project is uploaded."
